 3 │ Rust’s type system is robust, especially when it comes to handling lifetimes—particularly in functions that use references. Lifetimes are crucial for ensuring memory safety by preventing dangling pointers or data races. However, the explicit annotation of lifetimes can sometimes feel like an extra layer of complexity. Rust addresses this with three lifetime elision rules that automatically infer lifetimes for you when they’re safe to do so.
   ·                                                                                                                                                                                                                             ───┬───
