 11 │ 1. **Default Parameter Rule**: If a function has only one reference parameter, the lifetime is inferred as the longest-living (outermost) reference in the argument list. This rule assumes that the referenced value lives at least as long as the outermost borrowed reference.
    ·    ─────────────┬────────────
