 22 │ 2. **Multiple Reference Parameter Rule**: If a function has more than one reference parameter, Rust uses the following pattern to infer lifetimes: the first reference gets the default lifetime `'a`, the second gets `'b`, and so on. This rule helps disambiguate which references are related or independent of each other.
    ·    ──────────────────┬──────────────────
