 34 │ 3. **Return Type Rule**: If a function’s return type contains a reference and there are no parameters (or only multiple non-reference parameters), Rust infers the lifetime of the returned reference to be the same as the longest-living argument in the call site. This rule helps when the function’s behavior is tied to its input references.
    ·    ──────────┬─────────
